All Phase 0 Database-agent work is done. Summary below.

---

## WHAT I DID

**Migrations** in `supabase/migrations/` (timestamped, idempotent, identical across dev/staging/prod):

- `20260515000100_init.sql` — extensions (`pgcrypto`, `postgis`, `citext`), the 10 enum types (`meal_type`, `verification_status`, `request_status`, `booking_status`, `budget_tier`, `payment_status`, `escrow_status`, `message_type`, `review_subject_type`, `cancellation_party`), and the shared `set_updated_at()` trigger function.
- `20260515000200_users.sql` — `users` (1:1 with `auth.users`, two-mode flags, soft delete, guidelines acceptance), `companion_profiles` (rate snapshot, Stripe Connect fields, denormalized rating roll-up, `geography(Point, 4326)` service-area centre + radius), and `availability` (recurring weekly windows per meal type + timezone).
- `20260515000300_requests_and_bookings.sql` — `meal_requests` (seeker→companion, status machine source) and `bookings` (`request_id` 1:1, restaurant + budget tier set at confirmation, fee snapshotted from companion rate, completion/cancellation invariants enforced by CHECK constraints).
- `20260515000400_payments_messages_reviews.sql` — `payments` (1:1 with booking, Stripe identifiers only — no card data, escrow status independent of payment status, release/refund mutually exclusive), `messages` (booking-scoped, immutable, system vs user types), `reviews` (two-way, one-per-author-per-booking unique constraint, author≠subject).
- `20260515000500_indexes.sql` — GiST geo indexes on three geography columns, partial index on `verification_status='verified'`, plus FK/lookup btree indexes on the high-traffic axes (bookings by participant, messages by booking, reviews by subject, etc).
- `20260515000600_rls.sql` — RLS enabled on every public table. Policies per the model documented in `supabase/README.md`. Includes `public.is_booking_participant(uuid)` helper (`security definer`) used by message/payment policies.

**Seed data** in `supabase/seed/seed.sql` — four auth users (password `Password123!`), two verified companions (Ben, Cleo), one pending companion (Dan — RLS hides him from discovery), one fully-realised completed booking with payment, system + user messages, and two-way reviews, plus one pending request. Idempotent (`on conflict do nothing`).

**Shared types** in `lib/types/`:
- `enums.ts` — every enum as a TS string-literal union plus the `REQUEST_NEXT_STATES` / `BOOKING_NEXT_STATES` transition maps for the frontend.
- `database.ts` — full `Database` shape with `Row`/`Insert`/`Update` for all eight tables, GeoJSON Point typing, and the `is_booking_participant` function signature. Replaces the Foundations-scaffolded placeholder.
- `index.ts` — re-exports both.

**Docs** in `supabase/README.md` — entity diagram, enum table, geography model, RLS quick reference, and explicit "frozen contract" callout for downstream agents.

## WHAT I COULD NOT DO

- **Run the migrations.** Phase 0 explicitly forbids it — Foundations will provision the three Supabase projects in Phase 1, then `npm run db:migrate` (currently a stub) will be wired up.
- **Regenerate `database.ts` via `supabase gen types`.** No live project to introspect yet; hand-authored shapes are the interim contract. Plan: replace this file the first time migrations are applied against the dev project.
- **Type-check the new TS.** `node_modules` is not installed in this sandbox (`tsc: command not found`); Foundations owns dependency install. Types compile by review.
- **Commit locally.** The working directory is not a git repository yet (Foundations agent has not run `git init`). See manual checkpoint below.

